The paper deals with the recovery of jointly sparse multichannel signals, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of convex relaxation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the use of coherence, which is a measure of the correlation between the columns of a dictionary matrix, indicating a possible connection to cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
